Press Releases



Koolbridge Solar, Inc. Achieves First Round of Capital Investment






May 5, 2015, 2:12pm EDT














WRIGHTSVILLE BEACH, N.C., May 5, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Koolbridge Solar, Inc. announced it has closed their first round of initial outside investor fund raising for $500,000.  Effective immediately, the company has begun the second round equity raise of $1 million dollars to support the commercialization of its software and patented and patent pending solar products.

"The principal business of Koolbridge, Solar, Inc. is to design, develop and sell innovative electrical products that allow solar energy to be integrated into homes more efficiently and economically, to reduce energy bills, and to provide greater supply reliability," said, J. Stephen Burnett, Co-Founder, Chairman, CEO, and Director of Koolbridge Solar.   
"All of us at Koolbridge Solar are very pleased to see a tremendous acceptance of not only our advanced solar management technology by investors, but also a high vote of confidence in the great team that Koolbridge Solar has assembled to take this Company to the next level of growth and success," said Bill Griffin, Interim President & COO.   
About Koolbridge Solar, Inc.
The initial product that Koolbridge Solar is bringing to market is their Smart Load Center™.   This innovative and timely product maximizes the use of free solar energy when the sun is shining and only pulls power from the electrical grid when solar is not available.  
The Smart Load Center Provides:

Solutions that increase in-home solar efficiencies 
Solutions that increase the homeowner's ROI 
Solutions that complete the communications chain from utility to smart grid, to smart home, to smart appliances.
The Smart Load Center is a solar / utility energy breaker box that can automatically select the use of electrical power, circuit by circuit, from solar, the utility grid, batteries or a generator.  The automatic selection of power sources uses a microcontroller to activate the dynamic switching of each breaker circuit based on availability of utility and solar power; preset user priorities, battery charge status, time of day, instantaneous consumption, historical consumption patterns and weather conditions.    
For additional information about Koolbridge Solar, Inc. visit:www.koolbridgesolar.com
Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20150505/213979LOGO
To view the original version on PR Newswire, visit:http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/koolbridge-solar-inc-achieves-first-round-of-capital-investment-300077926.html
SOURCE  Koolbridge Solar, Inc.




